wikipedia_page.main: Louisa Porogovska (born 31 March 1987) is a British  freestyle wrestler. She competed for England in the women's freestyle 55 kg event at the 2014 Commonwealth Games where she won a bronze medal.

response: In the women's freestyle 55 kg category at the 2014 Commonwealth Games, Babita's first opponent in the quarter-finals was Kathryn Marsh of Scotland whom she beat 9–2, 4–0 (classification points 4:1). Her opponent in the semi-finals was Louisa Porogovska of England whom she beat 2–0 (classification points 5:0) – victory by fall (wrestling terminology). In the gold medal bout, she was up against Brittanee Laverdure of Canada whom she beat 5–0, 4–2 (classification points 3:1) to win the gold medal.
